%226a41bd3e-96dd-4a22-9dd0-fdba42bea736%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EShe%20needed%20my%20reassurance%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmom-connecting-with-teen-working-out-together-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etalked%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20night.%20I%20listened%20more%20than%20I%20spoke.%20She%20didn't%20need%20solutions%3B%20at%20least%20not%20right%20away.%20She%20needed%20to%20feel%20heard.%20She%20was%20hurt%20and%20confused%2C%20asking%20questions%20no%2013-year-old%20should%20have%20to%20sit%20with%3A%20%26quot%3BDid%20I%20do%20something%20wrong%3F%26quot%3B%20%26quot%3BWhy%20would%20someone%20just%20stop%20being%20my%20friend%3F%26quot%3B%20%26quot%3BWhat's%20wrong%20with%20me%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20so%2C%20I%20started%20there.%20With%20the%20reassurance%20that%20nothing%20was%20wrong%20with%20her.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20explained%20that%20sometimes%2C%20especially%20during%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fi-thought-my-teens-would-be-best-friends-they-arent-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eteenage%3C%2Fa%3E%20years%2C%20friendships%20shift.%20People%20change.%20Interests%20evolve.%20Sometimes%20people%20drift%20away%20without%20a%20clear%20reason%2C%20and%20while%20it%20hurts%2C%20it's%20not%20always%20about%20something%20we%20did%20or%20didn't%20do.%20That's%20a%20hard%20truth%20for%20anyone%20to%20accept%2C%20especially%20a%20young%20girl%20navigating%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhelp-kids-teens-decide-what-to-be-when-grow-up-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eidentity%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20belonging%2C%20and%20self-worth.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22b5fc872c-eec1-4874-93f4-2ecbc8c292a8%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20also%20needed%20to%20help%20her%20feel%20empowered%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20next%20few%20weeks%2C%20I%20watched%20her%20go%20through%20what%20I%20could%20only%20describe%20as%20a%20miniature%20heartbreak.%20She%20questioned%20herself.%20She%20cried%20quietly.%20She%20tried%20to%20reconnect.%20And%20when%20those%20attempts%20were%20met%20with%20indifference%2C%20she%20began%20to%20withdraw.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20when%20I%20gently%20stepped%20in%2C%20not%20to%20fix%20it%2C%20but%20to%20empower%20her.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20talked%20to%20her%20about%20conflict%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fthree-questions-that-get-teenagers-to-talk-to-me-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecommunication%3C%2Fa%3E.%20How%20it's%20okay%20to%20ask%20for%20clarity%2C%20and%20how%20to%20do%20it%20with%20confidence%20and%20kindness.%20We%20role-played%20what%20she%20could%20say%20if%20she%20wanted%20to%20have%20a%20conversation%20with%20her%20friend.%20I%20reminded%20her%20that%20while%20she%20can't%20control%20how%20someone%20else%20behaves%2C%20she%20can%20choose%20how%20she%20responds.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAbout%20a%20month%20later%2C%20just%20when%20it%20seemed%20like%20the%20chapter%20had%20quietly%20closed%2C%20her%20friend%20messaged%20her%20out%20of%20the%20blue%20and%20asked%20if%20she%20wanted%20to%20meet%20at%20the%20park.%20My%20daughter%20stared%20at%20the%20screen%20for%20a%20long%20moment.%20Then%2C%20calmly%2C%20she%20replied%2C%20%26quot%3BMaybe%20another%20time.%26quot%3B%20It%20wasn't%20petty%2C%20it%20was%20a%20boundary.%20One%20she'd%20chosen%20for%20herself%2C%20on%20her%20terms.%20I%20didn't%20say%20much%2C%20but%20inside%2C%20I%20swelled%20with%20pride.%20She%20wasn't%20waiting%20to%20be%20chosen%20or%20chasing%20after%20answers%20anymore.%20She%20had%20learned%20to%20weigh%20her%20own%20worth%2C%20without%20my%20interference.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22c95e3f57-eb02-4c4e-9db7-3cb54a9f0673%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EShe%20learned%20resilience%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20truth%20is%2C%20that%20experience%20shaped%20her%20in%20a%20way%20I%20never%20could%20have.%20It%20taught%20her%20resilience.%20It%20deepened%20her%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdiscipline-kids-empathy-different-than-how-i-grew-up-smacking-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eempathy%3C%2Fa%3E.%20It%20gave%20her%20the%20tools%20to%20navigate%20relationships%20with%20more%20awareness%20and%20maturity.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20parent%2C%20standing%20back%20was%20one%20of%20the%20hardest%20things%20I've%20ever%20done.%20But%20I%20learned%20that%20support%20doesn't%20always%20mean%20stepping%20in.%20Sometimes%20it%20means%20standing%20besides%2C%20holding%20space%2C%20and%20trusting%20that%20your%20child%20has%20what%20it%20takes%20to%20make%20it%20through%2C%20even%20when%20it%20hurts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20months%20later%2C%20my%20daughter%20still%20talks%20about%20that%20friendship%20occasionally.%20Not%20with%20bitterness%2C%20but%20with%20perspective.%20She's%20grown.%20She's%20more%20cautious%20about%20who%20she%20lets%20in%2C%20but%20also%20more%20open%20to%20new%20possibilities.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20I've%20grown%2C%20too.%20I've%20learned%20that%20part%20of%20raising%20emotionally%20strong%20children%20is%20letting%20them%20experience%20uncomfortable%20feelings.%20Not%20sheltering%20them%20from%20every%20storm%2C%20but%20equipping%20them%20with%20the%20confidence%20and%20tools%20to%20weather%20it.%20Because%20they%20won't%20remember%20whether%20we%20fixed%20the%20problem.%20They'll%20remember%20whether%20we%20stood%20with%20them%20as%20they%20figured%20it%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20in%20that%2C%20there%20is%20healing%20for%20both%20of%20us.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fteen-friend-troubles-mom-didnt-fix-problem-help-2025-4%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1745314081000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F680653e7c6ad288d147eacb2%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fw