0program%2C%20an%20employee%20handbook%2C%20and%20designated%20bots%20%E2%80%94%20an%20HR%20manager%20and%20chief%20technology%20officer%20%E2%80%94%20to%20contact%20for%20help.%20Inside%20the%20fake%20company%20called%20TheAgentCompany%2C%20an%20autonomous%20agent%20can%20browse%20the%20web%2C%20write%20code%2C%20organize%20information%20in%20spreadsheets%2C%20and%20communicate%20with%20coworkers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAgents%20have%20emerged%20as%20the%20next%20major%20frontier%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchatgpt-openai-ai-dictionary-help-understand-nvidia-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egenerative%20AI%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGoogle%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Amazon%2C%20OpenAI%2C%20and%20every%20other%20major%20tech%20company%20race%20to%20build%20them.%20Instead%20of%20executing%20one-off%20instructions%20like%20a%20chatbot%20would%2C%20agents%20can%20independently%20act%20on%20a%20person's%20behalf%2C%20make%20decisions%20on%20the%20go%2C%20and%20perform%20in%20unfamiliar%20environments%20with%20little%20to%20no%20intervention.%20If%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Feverything-you-need-to-know-about-chat-gpt-2023-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EChatGPT%3C%2Fa%3E%20can%20suggest%20a%20few%20vacuum%20cleaners%20to%20buy%2C%20its%20agentic%20counterpart%20theoretically%20could%20pick%20one%20and%20buy%20it%20for%20you.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENaturally%2C%20the%20promise%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-is-agentic-ai-agents-2024-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAI%20agents%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20captivated%20CEOs.%20In%20a%20Deloitte%20survey%20of%20over%202%2C500%20C-suite%20leaders%2C%20more%20than%20one-quarter%20of%20respondents%20said%20their%20organizations%20were%20exploring%20autonomous%20agents%20to%20a%20%26quot%3Blarge%20or%20very%20large%20extent.%26quot%3B%20Earlier%20this%20year%2C%20Salesforce's%20chief%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.axios.com%2F2025%2F01%2F22%2Fsalesforce-chief-ai-agents-davos%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esaid%3C%2Fa%3E%20today's%20CEOs%20will%20lead%20the%20last%20all-human%20workforces.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnvidia-ceo-ai-employees-workers-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENvidia's%20cofounder%20and%20CEO%3C%2Fa%3E%20Jensen%20Huang%20predicted%20every%20company's%20IT%20department%20will%20soon%20%26quot%3Bbe%20the%20HR%20department%20of%20AI%20agents.%26quot%3B%20OpenAI's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsam-altman-chatgpt-openai-ceo-career-net-worth-ycombinator-prepper-2023-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESam%20Altman%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20said%20that%20this%20year%2C%20AI%20agents%20will%20%26quot%3Bjoin%20the%20workforce.%26quot%3B%20But%20it's%20still%20unclear%20how%20well%20these%20agents%20can%20accomplish%20the%20tasks%20a%20company%20might%20need%20them%20to.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20test%20this%20out%2C%20the%20%3Cspan%3ECarnegie%20Mellon%3C%2Fspan%3E%20researchers%20instructed%20artificial%20intelligence%20models%20from%20Google%2C%20OpenAI%2C%20Anthropic%2C%20and%20Meta%20to%20complete%20tasks%20a%20real%20employee%20might%20carry%20out%20in%20fields%20such%20as%20finance%2C%20administration%2C%20and%20software%20engineering.%20In%20one%2C%20the%20AI%20had%20to%20navigate%20through%20several%20files%20to%20analyze%20a%20coffee%20shop%20chain's%20databases.%20In%20another%2C%20it%20was%20asked%20to%20collect%20feedback%20on%20a%2036-year-old%20engineer%20and%20write%20a%20performance%20review.%20Some%20tasks%20challenged%20the%20models'%20visual%20capabilities%3A%20One%20required%20the%20models%20to%20watch%20video%20tours%20of%20prospective%20new%20office%20spaces%20and%20pick%20the%20one%20with%20the%20best%20health%20facilities.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20results%20weren't%20great%3A%20The%20top-performing%20model%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fanthropic-claude-computer-use-ai-explainer-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAnthropic's%20Claude%3C%2Fa%3E%203.5%20Sonnet%2C%20finished%20a%20little%20less%20than%20one-quarter%20of%20all%20tasks.%20The%20rest%2C%20including%20Google's%20Gemini%202.0%20Flash%20and%20the%20one%20that%20powers%20ChatGPT%2C%20completed%20about%2010%25%20of%20the%20assignments.%20There%20wasn't%20a%20single%20category%20in%20which%20the%20AI%20agents%20accomplished%20the%20majority%20of%20the%20tasks%2C%20says%20Graham%20Neubig%2C%20a%20computer%20science%20professor%20at%20CMU%20and%20one%20of%20the%20study's%20authors.%20The%20findings%2C%20along%20with%20other%20emerging%20research%20about%20AI%20agents%2C%20complicate%20the%20idea%20that%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-is-an-ai-agent-depends-who-you-ask-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAI%20agent%20workforce%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20just%20around%20the%20corner%20%E2%80%94%20there's%20a%20lot%20of%20work%20they%20simply%20aren't%20good%20at.%20But%20the%20research%20does%20offer%20a%20glimpse%20into%20the%20specific%20ways%20AI%20agents%20could%20revolutionize%20the%20workplace.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3ETwo%20years%20ago%2C%20OpenAI%20released%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Farxiv.org%2Fpdf%2F2303.10130%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewidely%20discussed%20study%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20said%20professions%20like%20financial%20analysts%2C%20administrators%2C%20and%20researchers%20are%20most%20likely%20to%20be%20replaced%20by%20AI.%20But%20the%20study%20based%20its%20conclusions%20on%20what%20humans%20and%20large%20language%20models%20said%20were%20likely%20to%20be%20automated%20%E2%80%94%20without%20measuring%20whether%20LLM%20agents%20could%20actually%20do%20those%20jobs.%20The%20Carnegie%20Mellon%20team%20wanted%20to%20fill%20that%20gap%20with%20a%20benchmark%20linked%20directly%20to%20real-world%20utility.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20many%20scenarios%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fyale-alumni-spur-funding-ai-agent-startup-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAI%20agents%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20study%20started%20well%2C%20but%20as%20tasks%20became%20more%20complex%2C%20they%20ran%20into%20issues%20due%20to%20their%20lack%20of%20common%20sense%2C%20social%20skills%2C%20or%20technical%20abilities.%20For%20example%2C%20when%20prompted%20to%20paste%20its%20responses%20to%20questions%20in%20%26quot%3Banswer.docx%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20AI%20treated%20it%20as%20a%20plain%20text%20file%20and%20%3Cspan%3Ecouldn't%20add%20its%20answers%20to%20the%20document%3C%2Fspan%3E.%20Agents%20also%20routinely%20misinterpreted%20conversations%20with%20colleagues%20or%20wouldn't%20follow%20up%20on%20key%20directions%2C%20prematurely%20marking%20the%20task%20complete.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOther%20studies%20have%20similarly%20concluded%20that%20AI%20cannot%20keep%20up%20with%20multilayered%20jobs%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.library.hbs.edu%2Fworking-knowledge%2Fhow-humans-outshine-ai-in-adapting-to-change%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EOne%3C%2Fa%3E%20found%20that%20AI%20cannot%20yet%20flexibly%20navigate%20changing%20environments%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fblog.langchain.dev%2Freact-agent-benchmarking%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eanother%3C%2Fa%3E%20found%20agents%20struggle%20to%20perform%20at%20human%20levels%20when%20overwhelmed%20by%20tools%20and%20instructions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhile%20agents%20may%20be%20used%20to%20accelerate%20some%20portion%20of%20the%20tasks%20that%20human%20workers%20are%20doing%2C%20they%20are%20likely%20not%20a%20replacement%20for%20all%20tasks%20at%20the%20moment%2C%26quot%3B%20Neubig%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Carnegie%20Mellon%20study%20was%20far%20from%20a%20perfect%20simulation%20of%20how%20agents%20would%20work%20in%20the%20wild.%20Most%20proponents%20of%20agents%20envision%20them%20working%20in%20tandem%20with%20a%20human%20who%20could%20help%20course-correct%20if%20the%20AI%20ran%20into%20an%20obvious%20roadblock.%20The%20generation%20of%20agents%20that%20was%20studied%20is%20also%20not%20that%20skilled%20at%20carrying%20out%20humanlike%20tasks%20such%20as%20browsing%20the%20web.%20Newer%20tools%2C%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fopenai-launches-operator-ai-agent-book-reservations-buy-products-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EOpenAI's%20Operator%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20will%20likely%20be%20more%20adept%20at%20these%20tasks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20these%20limitations%2C%20the%20research%20offers%20something%20valuable%3A%20It%20points%20to%20what's%20coming%20next.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStephen%20Casper%2C%20an%20AI%20researcher%20who%20was%20part%20of%20the%20MIT%20team%20that%20developed%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faiagentindex.mit.edu%2Findex%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efirst%20public%20database%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20deployed%20agentic%20systems%2C%20says%20agents%20are%20%26quot%3Bridiculously%20overhyped%20in%20their%20capabilities.%26quot%3B%20He%20says%20the%20main%20reason%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-agents-errors-hallucinations-compound-risk-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAI%20agents%20struggle%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20accomplish%20real-world%20tasks%20reliably%20is%20that%20%26quot%3Bit%20is%20challenging%20to%20train%20them%20to%20do%20so.%26quot%3B%20Most%20state-of-the-art%20AI%20systems%20are%20decent%20chatbots%20because%20it's%20relatively%20easy%20to%20teach%20them%20to%20be%20nice%20conversational%20partners%3B%20it's%20harder%20to%20teach%20them%20to%20do%20everything%20a%20human%20employee%20can.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20TheAgentCompany%2C%20AI%20succeeded%20the%20most%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcareer-ladder-software-engineers-collapsing-ai-google-meta-coding-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esoftware%20development%20tasks%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20even%20though%20those%20are%20more%20difficult%20for%20humans.%20The%20researchers%20hypothesize%20this%20is%20because%20there's%20an%20abundance%20of%20publicly%20available%20training%20data%20for%20programming%20jobs%2C%20while%20workflows%20for%20admin%20and%20financial%20tasks%20are%20typically%20kept%20private%20within%20companies.%20There%20just%20isn't%20great%20data%20to%20train%20an%20AI%20on.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJeff%20Clune%2C%20a%20computer%20science%20professor%20at%20the%20University%20of%20British%20Columbia%20who%20helped%20build%20an%20agent%20for%20OpenAI%20that%20could%20use%20computer%20software%20like%20a%20human%2C%20thinks%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fproduct-managers-train-ai-agents-microsoft-chief-technology-officer-scott-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etraining%20AI%20agents%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20proprietary%20data%20from%20day-to-day%20activities%20and%20workflow%20patterns%20could%20be%20the%20key%20to%20improving%20their%20efficacy.%20That's%20exactly%20what%20a%20lot%20of%20companies%20are%20starting%20to%20do.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EMoody's%20is%20one%20of%20many%20major%20companies%20experimenting%20with%20training%20AI%20on%20in-house%20data.%20The%20116-year-old%20financial%20services%20firm%20is%20automating%20business%20analysis%20through%20agentic%20AI%20systems%2C%20which%20draw%20insights%20from%20decades%20of%20research%2C%20ratings%2C%20articles%2C%20and%20macroeconomic%20information.%20The%20training%20is%20designed%20to%20emulate%20how%20a%20human%20team%20would%20analyze%20a%20business%2C%20using%20carefully%20crafted%20instructions%20broken%20into%20independent%20steps%20by%20people%20experienced%20in%20the%20field.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20it's%20too%20early%20to%20tell%20how%20effective%20Moody's%20approach%20is%2C%20its%20managing%20director%20of%20AI%2C%20Sergio%20Gago%2C%20says%20the%20firm%20is%20actively%20exploring%20what%20kinds%20of%20work%20%E2%80%94%20like%20analyzing%20the%20financials%20of%20a%20small%20business%20%E2%80%94%20agents%20could%20take%20over.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESimilarly%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpharmaceutical-companies-embrace-ai-in-drug-discovery-efforts-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EJohnson%20%26amp%3B%20Johnson%3C%2Fa%3E%20tells%20Business%20Insider%20it%20was%20able%20to%20cut%20production%20time%20for%20the%20chemical%20processes%20behind%20making%20new%20drugs%20by%2050%25%20with%20fine-tuned%20in-house%20AI%20agents%20that%20could%20automatically%20adjust%20factors%20like%20temperature%20and%20pressure.%20Jim%20Swanson%2C%20J%26amp%3BJ's%20chief%20information%20officer%2C%20says%20the%20company%20is%20focused%20on%20training%20people%20to%20collaborate%20with%20AI%20agents.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJohns%20Hopkins%20scientists%20have%20created%20an%20Agent%20Laboratory%2C%20which%20leverages%20LLMs%20to%20automate%20much%20of%20the%20research%20process%2C%20from%20literature%20review%20to%20report%20writing%2C%20with%20human-provided%20ideas%20and%20feedback%20at%20each%20stage.%20%26quot%3BI%20think%20it%20won't%20be%20long%20before%20we%20trust%20AI%20for%20autonomous%20discovery%2C%26quot%3B%20Samuel%20Schmidgall%2C%20one%20of%20the%20Johns%20Hopkins%20scientists%2C%20says.%20Likewise%2C%20LG%20Electronics'%20research%20division%20developed%20an%20AI%20agent%20that%20it%20says%20can%20verify%20datasets'%20licenses%20and%20dependencies%2045%20times%20faster%20than%20a%20team%20of%20human%20experts%20and%20lawyers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20still%20unclear%20whether%20organizations%20can%20trust%20AI%20enough%20to%20automate%20their%20operations.%20In%20multiple%20studies%2C%20AI%20agents%20attempted%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-models-can-learn-deceptive-behaviors-anthropic-researchers-say-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eto%20deceive%20and%20hack%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20accomplish%20their%20goals.%20In%20some%20tests%20with%20TheAgentCompany%2C%20when%20an%20agent%20was%20confused%20about%20the%20next%20steps%2C%20it%20created%20nonexistent%20shortcuts.%20During%20one%20task%2C%20an%20agent%20couldn't%20find%20the%20right%20person%20to%20speak%20with%20on%20the%20chat%20tool%20and%20decided%20to%20create%20a%20user%20with%20the%20same%20name%2C%20instead.%20A%20BI%20investigation%20from%20November%20found%20that%20Microsoft's%20flagship%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmicrosoft-ai-artificial-intelligence-bet-doubts-marc-benioff-satya-nadella-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAI%20assistant%2C%20Copilot%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20faced%20similar%20struggles%3A%20Only%203%25%20of%20IT%20leaders%20surveyed%20in%20October%20by%20the%20management%20consultancy%20Gartner%20said%20Copilot%20%26quot%3Bprovided%20significant%20value%20to%20their%20companies.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBusinesses%20also%20remain%20concerned%20about%20being%20held%20responsible%20for%20their%20agents'%20mistakes.%20Plus%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fthomson-reuters-legal-win-ai-copyright-case-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecopyright%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20other%20intellectual%20property%20infringements%20could%20prove%20a%20legal%20nightmare%20for%20organizations%20down%20the%20road%2C%20says%20Thomas%20Davenport%2C%20an%20IT%20and%20management%20professor%20at%20Babson%20College%20and%20a%20senior%20advisor%20at%20Deloitte%20Analytics.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20direction%20things%20are%20heading%20looks%20different%20from%20what%20most%20people%20thought%20a%20few%20years%20ago.%20When%20AI%20first%20took%20off%2C%20a%20lot%20of%20jobs%20seemed%20to%20be%20on%20the%20chopping%20block.%20Journalists%2C%20writers%2C%20and%20administrators%20were%20all%20at%20the%20top%20of%20the%20list.%20So%20far%2C%20though%2C%20AI%20agents%20have%20had%20a%20hard%20time%20navigating%20a%20maze%20of%20complex%20tools%20%E2%80%94%20something%20critical%20to%20any%20admin%20job.%20And%20they%20lack%20the%20social%20skills%20crucial%20to%20journalism%20or%20anything%20HR-related.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENeubig%20takes%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flanguage-translator-uses-ai-wont-replace-adapt-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etranslation%20market%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20a%20precedent.%20Despite%20machine%20language%20translation%20becoming%20so%20accessible%20and%20accurate%20%E2%80%94%20putting%20translators%20at%20the%20top%20of%20the%20list%20for%20job%20cuts%20%E2%80%94%20the%20number%20of%20people%20working%20in%20the%20industry%20in%20the%20US%20has%20remained%20rather%20steady.%20A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.npr.org%2Fsections%2Fplanet-money%2F2024%2F06%2F18%2Fg-s1-4461%2Fif-ai-is-so-good-why-are-there-still-so-many-jobs-for-translators%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%26quot%3BPlanet%20Money%26quot%3B%20analysis%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20Census%20Bureau%20data%20found%20that%20the%20number%20of%20interpreters%20and%20translators%20grew%2011%25%20between%202020%20and%202023.%20%26quot%3BAny%20efficiency%20gains%20resulted%20in%20increased%20demand%2C%20increasing%20the%20total%20size%20of%20the%20market%20for%20language%20services%2C%26quot%3B%20Neubig%20says.%20He%20thinks%20that%20AI's%20impact%20on%20other%20sectors%20will%20follow%20a%20similar%20trajectory.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20the%20companies%20seeing%20massive%20success%20with%20AI%20agents%20are%2C%20for%20now%2C%20keeping%20humans%20in%20the%20loop.%20Many%2C%20like%20J%26amp%3BJ%2C%20aren't%20yet%20prepared%20to%20look%20past%20AI's%20risks%20and%20are%20focused%20on%20training%20staff%20to%20use%20it%20as%20a%20tool.%20%26quot%3BWhen%20used%20responsibly%2C%20we%20see%20AI%20agents%20as%20powerful%20complements%20to%20our%20people%2C%26quot%3B%20Swanson%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInstead%